  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7</p>\n<p>Place your hand flat onto the <strong>chicken breast<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\n<p>Slice in half as if you were cutting a burger bun, so you are left with 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> thinner pieces</p>\n<p>Peel and slice the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2144-Step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2144-Step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2144-Step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2144-Step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2144-Step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>oregano</strong> to a plate with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give it a good mix up</p>\n<p>Rub the <strong>chicken breast pieces</strong> with 1/2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong></p>\n<p>Add the <strong>chicken breast pieces</strong> to the plate and press down to coat in the <strong>oregano mix</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2144-Step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2144-Step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2144-Step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2144-Step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2144-Step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>coated chicken breast pieces</strong> to one side of a baking tray </p>\n<p>Add the <strong>sliced red onion</strong> to the other side of the tray with 1/2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 10-15 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the onions have softened – this is your <strong>herby chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2144-Step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2144-Step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2144-Step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2144-Step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2144-Step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, chop the <strong>capers</strong> finely</p>\n<p>Peel and finely grate the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2144-Step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2144-Step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2144-Step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2144-Step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2144-Step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> chopped capers</strong>, <strong>grated garlic</strong> (don't like raw garlic? Go easy!),<strong> Dijon mustard</strong>, <strong>natural yoghurt </strong>and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> to a small bowl</p>\n<p>Add <strong>half</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> [all]</span> the<strong> white wine vinegar </strong>with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]<strong> </strong></span><strong>cold water </strong>and season with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong></p>\n<p>Give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>Caesar dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2144-Step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2144-Step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
